Daisy Burrell https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daisy_Burrell 0 Daisy Burrell (16 June 1892 – 10 June 1982), real name Daisy Isobel Eaglesfield Ratton, was an English stage actress and Edwardian musical comedy performer who also appeared as a leading lady in silent films and in pantomime. In 1951 she appeared in The Golden Year, the first musical comedy produced for television.
